3.34. Mobile Routes - Stop Rating

  


Requirements

We would like to start tracking guests based on the quality of their items. To increase the objectivity of the item ratings, we are including a rating of the guest and the items.

  


We will replace the Status drop down on the Mobile Routes screen. To complete a stop, the driver will have these options:

  


![](data:image/png;base64,) Fulfilled  
---  
Guest  
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  
Items  
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  
  
  
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) Attempted  
  
  
![](data:image/png;base64,)Canceled  
  
  


It would then show an overlay with the icon, the Fulfilled/Attempted/Canceled text, and two big buttons:

  * Confirm
  * Cancel



  


These ratings will appear in the Stop detail if the current user has permission to see these ratings. To avoid bias for the pickup and delivery staff, this will only be visible to administrators.
